definition: cannot help/to be beyond control of
to follow/from/it is for...to/reason/cause/because of/due to/to/to leave it (to sb)/by (introduces passive verb)
to obtain/to get/to gain/to catch (a disease)/proper/suitable/proud/contented/to allow/to permit/ready/finished
structural particle: used after a verb (or adjective as main verb), linking it to following phrase indicating effect, degree, possibility etc
to have to/must/ought to/to need to

sentences.english: But that wasn't of your choosing.
You start off with a play and it never quite works out as you figured it would.
sentences.chinese: 比赛一开了场，这场球怎么打下去就完全由不得你了。

sentences.english: So life piled up the days on her, and was beyond her control.
sentences.chinese: 这就是生活给她堆砌的日子，由不得她。

sentences.english: Seiko can not help pondering the fine, the delivery time flies.
sentences.chinese: 由不得精工细琢磨了，交稿时间不等人。

sentences.english: Shut up, it is not decided by you.
NO: it is not yours to open buds into blossoms.
sentences.chinese: 不，催蓓蕾开花，那可由不得你。

sentences.english: But you don't get to pick what you like.
sentences.chinese: 可是，喜欢什么由不得你选。

sentences.english: For you to speak at this time.
